content:
Creating a React Native application that displays a list of all countries using a `FlatList` component involves several steps. Below, I'll guide you through a simple implementation:

1. **Set Up Your React Native Environment:**
   First, ensure you have Node.js and npm (or yarn) installed. Then, set up your React Native environment by following the [official React Native documentation](https://reactnative.dev/docs/environment-setup).

2. **Initialize a New React Native Project:**
   Use the following command to create a new React Native project:
   ```bash
   npx react-native init CountryListApp
   ```
   Navigate into your project directory:
   ```bash
   cd CountryListApp
   ```

3. **Install Required Packages:**
   You might not need any additional packages for this example, but if you want to fetch data from an API, you can use `axios` or `fetch`.

4. **Create a Component to Display the Country List:**
   Edit the `App.js` file to include the necessary code for displaying the list of countries.

   ```javascript
   import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react';
   import { View, Text, FlatList, StyleSheet } from 'react-native';

   const App = () => {
     const [countries, setCountries] = useState([]);

     useEffect(() => {
       const fetchCountries = async () => {
         try {
           const response = await fetch('https://restcountries.com/v3.1/all');
           const data = await response.json();
           setCountries(data);
         } catch (error) {
           console.error(error);
         }
       };

       fetchCountries();
     }, []);

     const renderItem = ({ item }) => (
       <View style={styles.item}>
         <Text style={styles.title}>{item.name.common}</Text>
       </View>
     );

     return (
       <View style={styles.container}>
         <FlatList
           data={countries}
           renderItem={renderItem}
           keyExtractor={(item) => item.cca3}
         />
       </View>
     );
   };

   const styles = StyleSheet.create({
     container: {
       flex: 1,
       marginTop: 50,
       paddingHorizontal: 20,
     },
     item: {
       backgroundColor: '#f9c2ff',
       padding: 20,
       marginVertical: 8,
     },
     title: {
       fontSize: 24,
     },
   });

   export default App;
   ```

5. **Run Your Application:**
   Run your app on your desired platform (iOS or Android) using the following command:
   ```bash
   npx react-native run-android
   ```
   or
   ```bash
   npx react-native run-ios
   ```

6. **Explanation:**
   - **State Management:** We use `useState` to manage the list of countries.
   - **Fetching Data:** We fetch data from the `https://restcountries.com/v3.1/all` API to get the list of countries.
   - **Rendering List:** We use the `FlatList` component to render the list of countries. Each country is displayed using the `renderItem` function, which returns a styled `View` containing the country name.

This simple setup should give you a basic React Native application displaying a list of countries using the `FlatList` component. You can further enhance it by adding search functionality, better styling, or additional features.
